---
description: Agent must verify and deliver working products — never delegate checks to the user
alwaysApply: true
---

# Deliver working products

The user does not run verification steps, smoke tests, or manual checks.

- Run migrations, seeds, tests, lint, builds, and smoke scripts yourself before reporting done.
- Fix failures yourself; do not end with "run X to verify" or "you can test by…".
- Deliver a working local stack (`./deploy.sh up` or docker compose) with confirmed health — verified by the agent, not the user.
- If the environment blocks verification (e.g. Docker resource limits), fix or work around it, then re-verify.
- Report outcomes as facts ("27 tests passed", "API healthy on :8100"), not instructions for the user.
